title: Can't use old keycard on Status Desktop
body:
# Bug Report

## Description

I have keycard initialized with Status Mobile app 1.20.x.

I was able to login on Status Desktop using the keycard several time. But after a while, I started getting an error "empty keycard".
@saledjenic mentioned this is because status mobile does not set metadata on keycard.

I accepted my fate and tried to initialized the keycard with Status Desktop

## Steps to reproduce

### Try recovering

1. Start Status Desktop
2. Select "lost keycard"
3. Select "reinitialize keycard"
4. Enter seed
5. Enter new keycard pin
6. Screen does not move forward

```
keycard - listing readers
keycard - waiting for card
keycard - card found at index 0
keycard - using reader ACS ACR39U ICC Reader 00 00
keycard - card protocol T1
keycard - verifyPin failed bad response 6f05: unexpected response
```

2. Select "lost keycard"
3. select "recover from seed" (or "continue without keycard", I dont' remember the wording)
4. Enter seed
